<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS -
        Component Removal - Preliminary Checks
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Preliminary Checks</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before removing components, determine gear backlash (crankshaft gear to camshaft gear), camshaft
                    end play, and crankshaft end play
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record camshaft gear-to-crankshaft gear backlash as follows :</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base on rear of engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip on a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
                <figure id="f2650803" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd03/d0304.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 290. Gear backlash check (camshaft gear to crankshaft gear)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate gear by hand and read indicator. Record backlash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds specified limits , replace camshaft gear.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reposition dial indicator and check camshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push camshaft toward the front of the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between the camshaft gear and crankcase. Lightly pry camshaft
                    forward. Compare dial indicator reading with specifications .
                </para>
                <figure id="f2650804" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd03/d0305.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 291. Camshaft end play</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Pry bar</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If end play exceeds specified limits, replace camshaft thrust plate.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on crankcase with indicator tip on the end of crankshaft flange as
                    shown.
                </para>
                <figure id="f2650805" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd07/d0713.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 292. Crankshaft end play</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft flange</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft forward with pry bar and zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft back and forth while reading dial indicator. Record end play.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
